metadata.label: Title
metadata.value: Book of hours (Latin and Dutch), BPL 2145

metadata.label: Author/creator
value: Canonesses Regular of St. Agnes, Maaseik
Canonesses Regular of St. Ursula & St. Anthony (Jerusalem), Venray

metadata.label: Content
metadata.value: Contains, alternating in Latin and Dutch translation: Hours of the Virgin (2r-46r), Antiphones and orations from Temporal and Sanctoral (47r-55v) Penitential psalms and Litany of the Saints (55v-68v), Office of the Dead (69r-94v) - Also contains prayers for the dying and for a funeral according to the use of the canonesses regular. - Also contains prayers for special masses and feast-days. - Also contains the passion from the Gospel of Matthew, in the translation of Johannes Scutken (139v-147v) and hymns. - For a complete overview of the content see BNM 435 and Stooker & 1997.

metadata.label: Note
value: Origin: Production/ownership by the canonesses regular of St. Agnes, Maaseik, based on the decorations, typical for this convent.
Also described by MMDC and A.W. Byvanckgenootschap (database RKD, The Hague).
